## 📊 **Data Types & Variables**

### **Primitive Types**
```
Integer (int): 🔢🔴 (Number action)
Float/Double: 🔢🔵 (Number potential)
String: 📝⚪ (Text flow)
Boolean: ✅❌ (True false)
Character: 📝🔴 (Text action)
Array: 📦🔢 (Container numbers)
Object: 📦🔗 (Container links)
Null/None: ⚫🚫 (Stillness forbidden)
```

### **Variable Declaration**
```
Create variable: 🔴📝 (Action write)
Assign value: ⚪➡️ (Flow to)
Constant: 🔒📝 (Lock write)
Global: 🌍📝 (World write)
Local: 🏠📝 (Home write)

Examples:
int x = 5; → 🔢🔴 📝⚪➡️ 🔢🔴 (Number action write flow to number action)
const PI = 3.14; → 🔒📝 ⚪➡️ 🔢🔵 (Lock write flow to number potential)
```

